1. Download Anaconda 

https://www.anaconda.com/download

2. Open Anaconda prompt and install all core dependencies

conda env create -f environment_gpu.yml
conda activate vamtoolbox-gpu

3. Install Ubuntu (if not already installed)
  
Download and install Ubuntu (e.g., Ubuntu 22.04 LTS or later).
https://ubuntu.com/tutorials/install-ubuntu-desktop#1-overview
Make sure your system boots into Ubuntu, updates are applied (`sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y`), and your GPU is physically installed and recognized.
   
4. Open Ubuntu and check the CUDA driver version of the system

nvidia-smi

5. Install PyTorch

pip install torch torchvision torchaudio --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu118

6. Install TIGRE

pip install git+https://github.com/CERN/TIGRE.git

7. # If the package exists in the local repo
pip install -e ./leapct

# Or install from a Git repository (replace with actual URL)
pip install git+https://github.com/your-lab/leapct.git

8. Test the installation 

python -c "import numpy, torch, cupy, imageio; print('Environment setup complete.')"
